      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(mcp): session-level MCP runtime cache + rollover cleanup",
        "body": "## Background\n\nMCP servers in the bundle config are spawned per agent run attempt. For stateful servers (e.g. a browser automation MCP), this means each message turn starts a fresh server with no memory of previous turns, making multi-turn stateful workflows impossible.\n\nAdditionally, when a conversation session rolls over (`/new`, `/reset`, idle timeout), the old session's MCP subprocesses are left running indefinitely — a resource leak proportional to session churn.\n\n> **Note**: This PR depends on #54957 (persistent MCP server lifecycle support), which introduces `createEmbeddedBundleMcpRuntime`.\n\n## Problem\n\n1. **State loss between turns**: A transient MCP server spawned in turn 1 is killed at the end of turn 1. Turn 2 spawns a fresh instance with no state from turn 1.\n2. **Subprocess leak on rollover**: When the user sends `/new`, the old session's MCP subprocesses keep running with no cleanup path.\n\n## Solution\n\n### Session-level MCP runtime cache (`run.ts`)\n\nAdds a `sessionMcpRuntimes: Map<sessionId, BundleMcpToolRuntime>` cache. On each agent run, the runtime is looked up by `sessionId`:\n- **Found**: reuse existing connections — no spawn overhead, state preserved across turns.\n- **Not found**: create a new runtime and cache it.\n\nThe runtime is **not** disposed at the end of an agent attempt. It lives until the session is explicitly cleaned up.\n\n### Targeted cleanup on session rollover\n\nAdds `disposeSessionMcpRuntime(sessionId)` which removes and disposes the runtime for exactly one session without affecting other live sessions. Called in:\n\n- `src/agents/agent-command.ts` — CLI `/new` and session ID change detection\n- `src/auto-reply/reply/session.ts` — auto-reply rollover (daily reset, idle timeout, explicit `/new`)\n\nProcess-level cleanup (`SIGINT` / `SIGTERM` / `exit`) disposes all cached runtimes.\n\n### Attempt-level injection (`run/attempt.ts`)\n\n`runEmbeddedPiAttempt` now accepts an optional `bundleMcpRuntime` param. When injected by the session cache, it skips per-attempt create/dispose, correctly scoping the runtime lifecycle to the session.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [ ] `src/auto-reply/reply/session.test.ts` — three new regression tests:\n  - `/new` calls `disposeSessionMcpRuntime` with the old session ID\n  - Stale (daily-reset) rollover calls dispose with the old session ID\n  - Fresh session does **not** call dispose\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
        "branch": "feat/mcp-session-cache",
